ABC Analyse

In [ ]:
# Group the data by 'Artikel' and sum the 'Umsatz' for each group
grouped_data6 = data.groupby('Artikel')['Umsatz'].sum()

# Sort the groups by the sum of 'Umsatz' in descending order
grouped_data6 = grouped_data6.sort_values(ascending=False)

# Calculate the total sales volume
total_sales = grouped_data6.sum()

# Calculate the cumulative percentage
grouped_data6_cumulative = grouped_data6.cumsum() / total_sales * 100

# Create the ABC classes
grouped_data6_class = pd.cut(grouped_data6_cumulative, [0, 80, 95, 100], labels=['A', 'B', 'C'])
abc_analysis = pd.concat([grouped_data6, grouped_data6_cumulative, grouped_data6_class], axis=1, keys=['Umsatz', 'Kumulative Prozentanteile', 'ABC-Klasse'])
abc_analysis.to_csv('abc_analysis.csv')

Umsatzverlauf pro Monat

In [ ]:
# import the data
csv_data = pd.read_csv('Datensatz_Lichtensteiger_(FS23).csv')
data3 = pd.DataFrame(csv_data)

# Convert the 'Zeitstempel' column to datetime format
data3['Zeitstempel'] = pd.to_datetime(data3['Zeitstempel'])

# Set the 'Zeitstempel' column as index
data3.set_index('Zeitstempel', inplace=True)

# Create a new dataframe with the monthly revenue
revenue = data3['Umsatz']

# Resample the data to monthly frequency
monthly_revenue = revenue.resample('M').sum()

# Create a new dataframe with the monthly revenue
monthly_revenue = pd.DataFrame({'Monate': monthly_revenue.index,'Umsatz': monthly_revenue.values})

# Plot the monthly revenue
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(20,6))
sns.lineplot(x='Monate', y='Umsatz', data=monthly_revenue, color='green',ax=ax, linewidth=2.5, label=f"Umsatz in CHF")

# Set the x-axis label and tick label rotation
plt.xticks(rotation=45)

# Set the x-axis tick locators and formatters to show all monthly dates
locator = mdates.AutoDateLocator(minticks=12, maxticks=48)
formatter = mdates.AutoDateFormatter(locator)
ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(locator)
ax.xaxis.set_major_formatter(formatter)
ax.legend(loc='upper left', fontsize=12, facecolor='white', framealpha=1)
sns.set_style('darkgrid')

# Show the plot
plt.show()

data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Zeitstempel'].dt.date)

# Group the data by year and month and sum the sales for each group
year_month_sales = data.groupby([data['Date'].dt.year, data['Date'].dt.month])['ArtikelNr'].sum()

# Loop through the years and plot the sales for each year in a separate plot
years = data['Date'].dt.year.unique()
for year in years:
    year_sales = year_month_sales[year]
    plt.plot(year_sales.index, year_sales.values, label=year)
    
plt.xlabel('Month')
plt.ylabel('Sales')
plt.title('Monthly Sales by Year')
plt.legend()
plt.show()

Monatliche Umsätze pro Jahr nach Produkt

In [ ]:
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Create a new column for the time component
data['Time'] = data['Zeitstempel'].dt.time

# Convert the 'Date' column to a datetime object
data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'], format='%Y-%m-%d')

# Group the data by 'ArtikelNr', year, and month, and sum the 'Menge' for each group
product_monthly_sales = data.groupby(['Artikel', data['Date'].dt.strftime('%Y-%m')])['Menge'].sum().reset_index()

# Pivot the data to have each product's sales per month as a separate column
product_monthly_sales_pivot = product_monthly_sales.pivot(index='Artikel', columns='Date', values='Menge')

# Plot the data for each product as a line chart
for product in product_monthly_sales_pivot.index:
    product_monthly_sales_pivot.loc[product].plot(label=product, legend=True)

plt.xlabel('Month')
plt.ylabel('Sales')
plt.title('Monthly Sales per Product')
plt.show()

abc_data = pd.read_csv('abc_analysis.csv')

# left join 'ABC-Klasse' with data by 'Artikel', drop all other columns from abc_data
data_abc = data.merge(abc_data[['Artikel', 'ABC-Klasse']], on='Artikel', how='left')

# select only articles with ABC-Klasse A
data_abc = data_abc.loc[data_abc['ABC-Klasse'] == 'A']

# import Feiertage.csv
feiertage = pd.read_csv('Feiertage.csv', parse_dates=['Zeitstempel'])

# merge feiertage with data_abc by date of Zeitstempel
data_abc = data_abc.merge(feiertage, on='Zeitstempel', how='left')

# group by day of year, year and 'Artikel' and sum up the 'Menge' column
data_abc = data_abc.groupby([data_abc['Zeitstempel'].dt.day_of_year, 'Artikel'])['Menge'].agg('sum').unstack()

# plot data_abc with a line for each Artikel
data_abc.plot(figsize=(15, 10), title="Verkäufe pro Tag für Artikel der ABC-Klasse A")

In-store vs Take-away Einkäufe

In [ ]:
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Load your dataset
df = pd.read_csv('Datensatz_Lichtensteiger_(FS23).csv')

# filter 'caffè crema' from df
# df = df[df['Artikel'] != 'caffè crema']

# Total number of products consumed in the store
num_consumed = len(df[df['Mwst Satz'] == 7.7])

# Total number of products taken away
num_taken_away = len(df[df['Mwst Satz'] == 2.5])

# Total number of products
total_num = len(df)

# Percentage of products consumed in the store
percent_consumed = num_consumed / total_num * 100

# Percentage of products taken away
percent_taken_away = num_taken_away / total_num * 100

# Display the results
print("Total number of products consumed in the store: ", num_consumed)
print("Total number of products taken away: ", num_taken_away)
print("Percentage of products consumed in the store: ", percent_consumed)
print("Percentage of products taken away: ", percent_taken_away)

# Number of each product consumed in the store or taken away
grouped = df.groupby('Artikel')

num_consumed_lst = []
num_taken_away_lst = []
product_lst = []
percent_consumed_lst = []
percent_taken_away_lst = []

for name, group in grouped:
    num_consumed = len(group[group['Mwst Satz'] == 7.7])
    num_taken_away = len(group[group['Mwst Satz'] == 2.5])
    total_num = len(group)
    percent_consumed = num_consumed / total_num * 100
    percent_taken_away = num_taken_away / total_num * 100
    num_consumed_lst.append(num_consumed)
    num_taken_away_lst.append(num_taken_away)
    product_lst.append(name)
    percent_consumed_lst.append(percent_consumed)
    percent_taken_away_lst.append(percent_taken_away)

# Create a bar plot
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10,6))

ax.barh(product_lst, percent_consumed_lst, label='Consumed in store', color='blue', alpha=0.5)
ax.barh(product_lst, percent_taken_away_lst, label='Taken away', color='orange', alpha=0.5, left = percent_consumed_lst)

ax.set_ylabel('Number of products')
ax.set_xlabel('Product')
ax.set_title('Number of products consumed in store or taken away')

ax.legend(loc='upper center')
plt.xticks(rotation=90)
plt.show()

import pandas as pd

# Load the dataset
avg_dataset = data.groupby(['Artikel'])['Menge'].mean().reset_index()

# Filter the dataset to only include rows where temperature is below zero
below_zero = data[data['Niederschlag Summe Tag'] == 0]
below_zero = below_zero.merge(avg_dataset, on='Artikel', how='left')
below_zero['Menge_adj'] = below_zero['Menge_x'] - below_zero['Menge_y']

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# define vars to look at
vars = ['Temperatur Schnitt Tag', 'Niederschlag Summe Tag', 'Globalstrahlung Schnitt Tag']

for var in vars:
    # Load the dataset
    temp_data = pd.read_csv("Datensatz_Lichtensteiger_(FS23).csv", parse_dates=['Zeitstempel'])
    
    # group by year and day of year and calculate the mean of the 'Temperatur Schnitt Tag' column
    temp_data = temp_data.groupby([temp_data['Zeitstempel'].dt.year, temp_data['Zeitstempel'].dt.week])[var].mean().unstack(level=0).reset_index().drop(['Zeitstempel'], axis=1)

    plt.figure(figsize=(20, 10))

    for year in range(2018,2023):
        plt.plot(temp_data.index, temp_data[year], label=year, alpha=0.5)

    # line with mean per week
    plt.plot(temp_data.index, temp_data.mean(axis=1), label='Durchschnitt alle Jahre', color='black')

    plt.legend()
